doctype html
head
  title ED2TTS
  meta(charset='utf-8')
  meta(name='viewport' content='width=device-width, initial-scale=1, shrink-to-fit=no')
  link(rel='stylesheet' href='https://stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.4.1/css/bootstrap.min.css' integrity='sha384-Vkoo8x4CGsO3+Hhxv8T/Q5PaXtkKtu6ug5TOeNV6gBiFeWPGFN9MuhOf23Q9Ifjh' crossorigin='anonymous')
body
  .navbar.bg-dark.navbar-expand-lg.navbar-dark
    a.navbar-brand(target="_blank" href="/") EncoreDecks to Tabletop Simulator (ED2TTS)
  .container
    .col-xl-12.py-md-3.pl-md-5.bd-content
      .jumbotron
        h1 Export your EncoreDecks to TTS
        p.lead ED2TTS creates a jpg of your deck in a format that is suitable for importing into Tabletop Simulator.
        img.img-fluid(src="/deck/ZT1ZXFQkp" alt="An example image created by ED2TTS. The image consists of 50 Weiss Schwarz cards arranged side by side in a 10x5 mosaic.")
      
      h2 
        span.bd-content-title Usage
      p
        | To get started, choose a deck on 
        a(target="_blank" href='//encoredecks.com/') encoredecks.com
        |  that you would like to import into Tabletop Simulator.

      p
        | For example, we will use 
        a(target="_blank" href="https://www.encoredecks.com/deck/ZT1ZXFQkp") My First Miku Deck
        | . In this case, the URL is https://www.encoredecks.com/deck/ZT1ZXFQkp. From the URL we can see that the 
        | Encoredecks Deck ID is #[strong ZT1ZXFQkp]. 
        
        
      p
        | Simply copy & paste the Encoredecks Deck ID below, and this website will generate a deck image which is suitable for importing into Tabletop Simulator.
        
      h2 
        span.bd-content-title Example
      
      p
        | https://www.encoredecks.com/deck/ZT1ZXFQkp becomes 
        a(target="_blank" href=`//${domain}/deck/ZT1ZXFQkp`) #{domain}/deck/ZT1ZXFQkp
        | . This URL can be pasted directly into the custom deck creation menu in Tabletop Simulator as demonstrated below.

      img.img-fluid(src="/custom-deck-example.jpg" style="width: 50%")

      h2 
        span.bd-content-title Future Improvements
      ul
        li hi-res card images.
        
      h2 
        span.bd-content-title Author
      p Chris Grimmett #[a(href="mailto:chris@grimtech.net") chris@grimtech.net]

